SECTION 3. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-7-202(g), is amended by deleting
the subsection and substituting the following:
(1)
(A) The commission shall establish a review committee to aid in
development or revision of the higher education master plan, state financial aid,
and funding formula. The committee consists of the executive director of the
Tennessee higher education commission, the chancellor of the board of regents,
the president of the University of Tennessee system, each president of a board
of regents state university, the commissioner of finance and administration, the
comptroller of the treasury, the chairs of the standing committees on education
and finance, ways and means of the senate, the chair of the standing committees
of the house of representatives having jurisdiction over education, the chair of the
standing committees of the house of representatives having jurisdiction over
finance, and the directors of the office of legislative budget analysis, or their
designees.
(B) In addition to the committee members established in subdivision
(g)(1)(A), the committee also consists of the president of the Tennessee
Independent Colleges and Universities Association, but the president of the
Tennessee Independent Colleges and Universities Association only serves on
the committee for the development or revision of the higher education master
plan and for state financial aid.
(2) The committee shall review the funding formula components, as well as
identify needed revisions, additions, or deletions to the formula. The committee shall
also ensure that the funding formula is linked to the goals and objectives of the master
plan.
(3) The review committee shall meet at least annually.
